This paper discusses the development of question answering systems that can understand natural language constructions for various domains, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) research. The paper also focuses on auto-completion for query formulation, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) research. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of semantic parsing systems, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DB (Databases).
